            <p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span style="color: #ff0000;">Fair Information Practices</span></strong></p>
            <p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000000;">The Fair Information Practices Principles form the backbone of privacy law in the United States and the concepts they include </span><span style="color: #000000;">have played a significant role in the development of data protection laws around the globe. Understanding the Fair </span><span style="color: #000000;">Information Practice Principles and how they should be implemented is critical to comply with the various privacy laws that </span><span style="color: #000000;">protect personal information.</span><span style="color: #000000;">In order to be in line with Fair Information Practices we will take the following responsive action, should a data breach </span><span style="color: #000000;">occur:</span></p>
